race.comment: ALBERTVILLE (5) resumes for his second preparation having promised plenty last time in, winning two in a row as favourite before perhaps needing a break when beaten as an even money chance in Adelaide. Jamie Melham has travelled to ride him in the past and does so again here which is worth noting. He can improve again this preparation and add to his record. YOLO (9) resumes having won impressively first up at Pakenham last time in. He can mix his form but the ability is there. Can return in winning form. MIDNIGHT DEVIL (4) has been out of the money in recent runs including last time out when eighth over 1214m at Geelong three weeks ago. Drops in class and from the good draw has claims. COMMANDS SUCCESS (7) returns from a lay-off. Placed in a recent Wangaratta jump-out. Opened last campaign with a fourth at Wangaratta over 1000m. In the mix.
